Privacy Policy

Last updated: April 7, 2025

1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how HearCalc ("the App") collects, uses, and protects anonymous usage data to improve your experience. By using the App, you agree to the collection and processing of this data as described below.

2. Data Collection
We collect anonymous usage data, which may include:

Basic usage statistics (e.g., feature usage, session duration)

General location data (city, region, country derived from your IP address)

Device information (e.g., device model, operating system)

Error reports and crash logs
We do not collect or store any personal information that could directly identify you.

3. Data Usage
The anonymous data is used solely to:

Analyze how users interact with the App

Improve performance, features, and the overall user experience

Identify areas for enhancement and new feature development

Ensure proper functionality across various devices and regions

4. Third-Party Services
We use third-party services such as Firebase and Google Analytics to collect and analyze this data. These services process data in accordance with their own privacy policies. No personal data is shared with any third parties.

5. Data Storage and Security
Anonymous usage data is stored securely using industry-standard measures. Data is retained only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, and all data remains anonymized to protect your privacy.

6. User Rights
Since no personally identifiable information is collected, there is no personal data linked to your identity. If you have any questions or concerns about our data practices, please contact us using the information provided in Section 8.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be posted within the App and on our website. Your continued use of the App after any changes signifies your acceptance of the revised policy.

Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
